Ri referred to a joint statement from Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first ever summit between a sitting U.S. president and a North Korean leader in Singapore on June 12, where Kim vowed to work “nuclear disarmament on the Korean peninsula,” while Trump vowed to guarantee North Korea’s security.
North Korea has called for a formal end to the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States has said Pyongyang must first give up its nuclear weapons.
